CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 17, 1958, pg. 5 reads: "High-Ranking Officers - Seated at the head of the luncheon table at the dinner of the Prince Hall Masons, Monday afternoon, at the Hotel Fort Pitt, are (left to right) William Roy, Most Puissant Grand Secretary General of the Southern Jurisdiction of the Prince Hall Masons; Leland D. French, of Cleveland, First Lieut. Commander of the Northern Jurisdiction; George W. Crawford, of New Haven, Conn., Most Puissant Sovereign Grand Commander; John Dawson, Grand marshal of Indianapolis, and John G. Lewis of Louisiana, Lieutenant Commander of the Southern Jurisdiction."
TitMainTitle: William Roy, Leland D. French, George W. Crawford, John Dawson, and John G. Lewis, seated at banquet table in Fort Pitt Hotel for the 75th Annual Session of the United Supreme Council of 33-Degree Masons
